    "question": "In a scenario where there are \\( a = 4 \\) men and \\( b = 6 \\) women, if \\( n = 10 \\) chips are distributed randomly, what is the probability that the total number of chips given to the men is an even number? Use the recurrence relation provided in the text to find \\( P(10) \\).",
    "solution": "To find \\( P(10) \\), we will use the recurrence relation given in the text:\n\n\\[\nP(n) = \\frac{b}{a + b} P(n-1) + \\frac{a}{a + b} (1 - P(n-1))\n\\]\n\nGiven \\( a = 4 \\) and \\( b = 6 \\):\n\n1. Calculate \\( P(0) \\):\n   \\[\n   P(0) = 1 \\quad \\text{(since 0 is even)}\n   \\]\n\n2. For \\( n = 1 \\):\n   \\[\n   P(1) = \\frac{6}{10} P(0) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(0)) = 0.6 \\times 1 + 0.4 \\times 0 = 0.6\n   \\]\n\n3. For \\( n = 2 \\):\n   \\[\n   P(2) = \\frac{6}{10} P(1) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(1)) = 0.6 \\times 0.6 + 0.4 \\times 0.4 = 0.36 + 0.16 = 0.52\n   \\]\n\n4. For \\( n = 3 \\):\n   \\[\n   P(3) = \\frac{6}{10} P(2) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(2)) = 0.6 \\times 0.52 + 0.4 \\times 0.48 = 0.312 + 0.192 = 0.504\n   \\]\n\n5. For \\( n = 4 \\):\n   \\[\n   P(4) = \\frac{6}{10} P(3) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(3)) = 0.6 \\times 0.504 + 0.4 \\times 0.496 = 0.3024 + 0.1984 = 0.5008\n   \\]\n\n6. For \\( n = 5 \\):\n   \\[\n   P(5) = \\frac{6}{10} P(4) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(4)) = 0.6 \\times 0.5008 + 0.4 \\times 0.4992 = 0.30048 + 0.19968 = 0.50016\n   \\]\n\n7. For \\( n = 6 \\):\n   \\[\n   P(6) = \\frac{6}{10} P(5) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(5)) = 0.6 \\times 0.50016 + 0.4 \\times 0.49984 = 0.300096 + 0.199936 = 0.500032\n   \\]\n\n8. For \\( n = 7 \\):\n   \\[\n   P(7) = \\frac{6}{10} P(6) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(6)) = 0.6 \\times 0.500032 + 0.4 \\times 0.499968 = 0.3000192 + 0.1999872 = 0.5000064\n   \\]\n\n9. For \\( n = 8 \\):\n   \\[\n   P(8) = \\frac{6}{10} P(7) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(7)) = 0.6 \\times 0.5000064 + 0.4 \\times 0.4999936 = 0.30000384 + 0.19999744 = 0.50000128\n   \\]\n\n10. For \\( n = 9 \\):\n    \\[\n    P(9) = \\frac{6}{10} P(8) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(8)) = 0.6 \\times 0.50000128 + 0.4 \\times 0.49999872 = 0.300000768 + 0.199999488 = 0.500000256\n    \\]\n\n11. Finally, for \\( n = 10 \\):\n    \\[\n    P(10) = \\frac{6}{10} P(9) + \\frac{4}{10} (1 - P(9)) = 0.6 \\times 0.500000256 + 0.4 \\times 0.499999744 = 0.3000001536 + 0.1999998976 = 0.5000000512\n    \\]\n\nThus, the probability \\( P(10) \\) that the total number of chips given to the men is an even number is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{0.5000000512}\n\\]",
